Adults only live for a season, which they feed, mate, lay eggs, and die. An interesting part is that the females grow cysts with the eggs that can lie dormant and viable for decades and even centuries. California Fairy Shrimp are the longest fairy shrimp.

A vibrant feature is their red eyes. They are active during spring time and are near threatened.

Habitat: Prairie Falcons are typically found in open hills, plains, prairies, grasslands and deserts. Also they can be found in fairly dry open country above the tree line, high in the mountains. In the winter, they can be found living in cultivated fields, lakeshores, and desert scrub. They avoid forested country and are rare on the immediate coast.
Identification: The Prairie Falcon is a large falcon in size, it can be seen as the same size as a medium-sized hawk with an average length of 40 cm, wingspan of approximately 1 meter, and average weight of 720 g. The coloration in its feathers is pale brown to gray. They are a medium-large sized falcon of western North America.
Name: Prairie Falcon
Overview: During their hunt the Prairie Falcon often uses a surprise attack on its prey by flying fast and low over the ground.  Adult Prairie Falcon are extremely territorial during the mating season and will fight off intruding with frequent stoops, loud sounds, and tail chases.

Overview:
Invasive species.
